.TH AGENT-HOOK-SESSION-END-CLAUDE 1 "2026-06-30" "agentguard" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
agent-hook-session-end-claude \- Claude-specific session-end maintenance
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B agent-hook-session-end-claude
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B agent-hook-session-end-claude
is sourced by
.BR agent-hook-session-end (1)
when the active runtime is Claude. It is not a standalone hook adapter and
should not be configured directly as the session-end command.
.PP
The extension can name untitled Claude sessions through
.BR claude-session-name (1)
while the generic hook owns stdin parsing, extension loading, and final JSON
emission.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
The extension completed or had no Claude-specific work to do.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR claude-session-name (1),
.BR agent-hook-session-end (1)
